<br>
By your reasoning, Bene, the USA should never have entered WW2.  We should have tried to find a “peaceful” solution to Hitler’s reign of terror over millions of innocent Jewish people and the conquest of the rest of the world.  There is only one difference between the Nazis and the terrorists of today.  The Nazis were at least bold enough to stand by their atrocities.   The terrorists have not even come forward yet to claim responsibility.  COWARDS!  <br>
<br>
These people, the terrorist, hate the USA with a white hot passion.  There is nothing the US can do to change that.  We forgive them, they hate us, we strike, they hate us.  They hate everything the USA is.  Our morals, our ideals, our wealth and even our poverty.<br>
<br>
The USA was right to cross the ocean, storm Normandy and crush the Nazis in WW2.  Yes innocent people died.  Yes, many, many good US soldiers died.  Yes, it was sad to have to kill tens of thousands of Germans, both soldiers and civilians.  But in the end, it was what needed to be done to wipe out an incredible evil… the evil of Adolf Hitler and his Third Reich.  (Please note, Germans are not evil, just Nazis who followed Hitler in his horrifying assault on the world)<br>
<br>
The USA has spend billions of dollars in peaceful anti-terrorist actions over the last 20 years.  For over 200 years, the USA has been free from terrorism on our soil.  Our government has been stellar in keeping this nation safe from senseless, ruthless attacks against innocent civilians when other governments, just as noble, have not been able to.  But eventually those terrorist would break through and strike at the heart of the USA.   And all the money, all the precautions, all the lives devoted to the defense of this great nation could not stop that jet from crashing into the side of one of the greatest structures ever built by mankind, the World Trade Center, killing more people than has ever been killed before in a terrorist attack.  And for what?  To send a message to the USA that we are evil?  To tell us that they hate us, our way of life?  That is exactly the reason.    HEY… Send us a F&amp;%$ing post card with the message then let BOTH sides live in peace.  But that is not their way.  Terrorism has grown more and more bold, ruthless and aggressive in the last decade.  <br>
