I normally consider myself an idealist.  In general I'm left leaning on topics such as this, I prefer discussion and diplomacy.<br>
<br>
But, for 20 years we've tried that.<br>
<br>
The entire Middle East region has a long and illustrious history of harboring, supporting and cheering terrorism.  They have been a thorn in much of the world's side.<br>
<br>
On 9/11 they stepped too far.  Until now they've remained small in focus and on a scale we largely had to ignore.<br>
<br>
What we need now is basically the unthinkable.  But, it's honestly the only way.  We need a full scale military assault to break the spine of the governments and schemes that support these organizations.  This may scatter them to the wind, netting us more enemeies, but in the end they'll be far less effective as an emeny.  Following this assault we need economic sanctions and cooperation from the international community to show that these actions are not acceptable.  <br>
<br>
Then we rebuild them as we have any other nation that we've decimated.<br>
<br>
I'd rather fight a dozen enemies wielding guns and bazookas then 1 well funded army that slings airliners at skyscrapers.  The world community can assimilate the dozen smaller enemies.  But it takes a concerted and committed force to tackle the 1.<br>
<br>
